<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="799" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d799">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6511/1028</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <p rend="center">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>His Majesty’s Ambassador presents his compliments to the Secretary of
                            State and has the honour to acknowledge the receipt of Mr. Hull’s note
                            of April 10th<note n="12" xml:id="d799fn12">Not printed.</note>
                            regarding the return to Europe of Admiral Alberto Lais, former Naval
                            Attaché at the Italian Embassy in Washington, and his two Italian naval
                            orderlies, Gaetano Canepa and Giovanni Burlo.</p>
                        <pb facs="0817" n="805" xml:id="pg_805"/>
                        <p>This matter has been referred to His Majesty’s Government who have now
                            authorized Lord Halifax to give the assurance that the British
                            authorities will not attempt to prevent the return of Admiral Lais or
                            his orderlies to Europe.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-17">April 17,
                                    1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>